The Alex Jones Show
Friday, 28 June 2013

Show Description
................

From the Infowars web site :: On this Friday, June 28 edition of The Alex Jones Show, Alex exposes the joke of gun control after a nanny cam captured the brutal beating of unarmed New Jersey woman. 

Authorities have now begun the mass purging of the First Amendment by labeling Americans' sarcastic comments as "terrorist threats." A Texas teenager has been behind bars since March after a Canadian woman phoned police over a crude joke he made in an on-line game. 

The cyber-industrial complex is already well on its way in the purging of the Fourth Amendment, labeling the domestic spy grid as "national security." 

Gerald Celente, financial forecaster and publisher of The Trends Journal, joins Alex in studio to discuss the implications of this privacy-killing industry, spending over $80 billion a year and employing over 835,000 contractors.
